main event: A civilian witness in Alexandria, Virginia observed a bright, disc-shaped object in the sky on April 15, 1966.
interesting points: The object appeared to be larger and brighter than the moon, and was cloaked in a hazy atmosphere.
The object initially remained stationary for about 13 minutes, then slowly moved upward and to the east before disappearing from view.
The witness reported that the object changed shape during the observation, and there was no noise, trail, or different colors observed.
The witness worked for the Director of Intelligence of the 9th Air Force from 1956 to 1958 and had experience typing similar reports.
The document includes four sketches or illustrations depicting different stages or shapes of the unidentified flying object.
